    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-20T04:10:48+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-20T04:10:48+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-19T17:40:48Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-19T17:40:48Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure will persist across the state. The high pressure centre will become established in the Tasman Sea over the weekend ahead of a cold front early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW012" description="Lower Eyre Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-20T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-21T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-19T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-20T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog near the west coast. Light winds becoming south to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning. Daytime maximum temperatures in the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:10am to 4:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 8 [Very High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-03-21T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-20T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of fog in the early morning. Mostly sunny day. Winds southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending southeast to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the middle of the day then tending southeasterly in the late afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 12 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 29.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Sunny afternoon. Light winds becoming southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-24T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-23T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Sunny morning. The chance of morning fog near the east coast. Slight chance of a shower in the afternoon. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending southeast to southwesterly during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 15 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
